---
const title = 'Tailwind templates and component kits';
const description = 'Overview of official Tailwind CSS templates and popular community UI kits with links.';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={description} />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/global.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header>
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      <p>{description}</p>
      <nav>
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/plans">Plans</a>
        <a href="/index-left">Left-aligned hero</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section>
        <h2>Official Tailwind resources</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <a href="https://tailwindui.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tailwind UI</a> — premium, production‑ready components and page examples by the Tailwind team.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://tailwindcss.com/docs" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tailwind Docs Examples</a> — small, focused examples embedded throughout the docs.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://play.tailwindcss.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tailwind Play</a> — online editor with many shared examples you can fork.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://headlessui.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Headless UI</a> — unstyled, accessible primitives for React/Vue that pair well with Tailwind.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss-templates" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Starter templates (community)</a> — assorted open templates collected by the community.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Popular community templates and UI kits</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <a href="https://daisyui.com/components/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">daisyUI</a> — large set of themed components as Tailwind plugin.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://flowbite.com/docs/components/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Flowbite</a> — component library (free + pro) with Tailwind styling.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://www.hyperui.dev/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">HyperUI</a> — free Tailwind components/snippets.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://preline.co/docs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Preline UI</a> — extensive Tailwind component set.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://merakiui.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Meraki UI</a> — free Tailwind components.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://tailgrids.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">TailGrids</a> — templates and UI blocks (free + pro).
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://tailblocks.cc/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tailblocks</a> — drag‑and‑drop page sections.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://tails.buompris.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tails</a> — page section blocks for Tailwind.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://ui.shadcn.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">shadcn/ui</a> — component blueprints using Tailwind + Radix (primarily for React with @tailwindcss/forms/typography).
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="note"><small>Note: Some kits target specific frameworks (React/Vue/Nuxt/Next). Since this site uses Astro, you can still use most Tailwind CSS markup directly, but framework‑specific interactivity may need adapters.</small></p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Starter projects and themes</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <a href="https://github.com/withastro/astro/tree/main/examples" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Astro examples</a> — many examples that can be styled with Tailwind.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://themes.stackbit.com/?framework=tailwindcss" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Stackbit Themes</a> — filter for Tailwind‑based themes.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://jamstackthemes.dev/ssg/astro/?s=tailwind" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Jamstack Themes</a> — Astro + Tailwind starters from the community.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
      <p>Compiled list of Tailwind template resources. Last updated 2025‑09‑29.</p>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
